During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders discussed various topics including the opioid crisis, a new initiative to empower women in Latin America, the confirmation hearing of Secretary of State-designee Mike Pompeo, a pardon issued by President Trump to Scooter Libby, ongoing conversations about a potential strike in Syria, and James Comey's new book. Sanders defended the President's attacks on Comey, criticized the former FBI director for leaking classified information, and reiterated that the dossier on Trump was false opposition research funded by the Clinton campaign. She also addressed the Justice Department Inspector General's report on Andrew McCabe and expressed concern about the situation involving Missouri Governor Eric Greitens. Finally, Sanders mentioned that trade and North Korea will be discussed during the upcoming summit with Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe.